The Confederation of African Football (CAF) is holding a seminar on the development of football competitions and infrastructure in Africa today at the Mohammed VI Football Complex, Sale, Morocco. FIFA president Gianni Infantino is expected to join CAF president Ahmad Ahmad and Fouzi Lekjaa, Morocco FA boss, to deliver the opening remarks. Infantino is also expected to give a presentation on the format of competitions while Anthony Baffoe, CAF DG in Charge of Football and Development, will present a paper on the current state and the standardisation of stadia. A presentation on refereeing will be done by FIFAâ€™s Head of Refereeing Department Massimo Busacca while breakout sessions on the financing of the development of football competitions and infrastructure in Africa and stadia inspection would be organised later.